            "id": "4566792",
            "title": "3 things to look forward to on Friday",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\" data-eci=\"true\">U.S. stocks ended lower on Thursday as investors could not shake off heightened oil prices and the ongoing war in Iran affecting the commodities.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The S&amp;P 500 (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SP500#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Index\">SP500</a>) ended -0.3%, while the Nasdaq Composite (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COMP:IND\" title=\"NASDAQ Composite Index\">COMP:IND</a>) finished -0.3%, and the Dow (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DJI\" title=\"Dow Jones Industrial Average Index\">DJI</a>) closed -0.4%.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The benchmark 10-year Treasury yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) was 1 basis point lower at 4.26%, while the 2-year Treasury yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) rose 2 basis points to 3.80%.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, crude oil futures (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CL1:COM#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"Crude Oil Futures\">CL1:COM</a>) were slightly lower at $94.9, while <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4565814-brent-crude-spikes-to-108-after-iran-says-energy-industry-attacked#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Brent futures\">Brent futures</a> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CO1:COM#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"Brent Futures\">CO1:COM</a>) were at $107.5 per barrel.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Gold (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XAUUSD:CUR\" title=\"Gold Spot Price\">XAUUSD:CUR</a></span>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4566636-gold-slides-5-and-breaks-key-100-day-ma-as-safe-haven-demand-fades#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">dropped</a> -3.4% to around $4,650 as safe-haven demand faded.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now here are three things for investors to focus on Friday:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Chinese electric vehicle manufacturer XPeng (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XPEV\" title=\"XPeng Inc.\">XPEV</a></span>) reports on Friday. The company closed +2% and saw a seven-day winning streak last week. Although it is down 5.6% year-to-date, its shares have risen 8.4% from a month ago. Morgan Stanley recently published positive remarks on its VLA 2.0 autonomous driving system, and Seeking Alpha analyst <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4862203-xpeng-not-just-a-car-company#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Michael Ngan\">Michael Ngan</a> said the company’s performance in the second half of 2024 and throughout 2025 continued to highlight its growth potential.</li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">The gold spot price (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XAUUSD:CUR\" title=\"Gold Spot Price\">XAUUSD:CUR</a>) slid 3.4% on Thursday to around $4,650 per ounce, its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4566636-gold-slides-5-and-breaks-key-100-day-ma-as-safe-haven-demand-fades\">weakest level since mid-January</a>. This has pushed prices below the key 100-day moving average, showing weak technical momentum and continued downside pressure in the near term. Investors will continue to monitor the traditional safe-haven asset as inflation fears grow.</li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">U.S. Treasury yields surged Thursday, with the 2-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) jumping 9 basis points to 3.87%—its highest level in over seven months—after the Federal Reserve held rates steady at 3.50%-3.75%. In addition, the 10-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) rose to 4.30% at some point, and the 30-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US30Y\" title=\"United States 30-Year Bond Yield\">US30Y</a>) climbed 4.90%, as investors scaled back hopes for near-term rate cuts and adjusted to a higher-for-longer interest rate environment. Yields have since lowered, but their trajectory will be watched.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
